<br>
Microsoft didn't become a behemoth by being altruistic.<br>
<br>
Neither did IBM.<br>
<br>
Even Dell, with their once vaunced lifetime phone support for free, realized they were losing money in a major way and severely altered the terms of their support.<br>
<br>
Verant would be a small fish as far as Sony subsidiaries go. I doubt anyone high up in Sony really pays attention to the CS issues with EQ.<br>
<br>
Why should they?<br>
<br>
Sony is, and, always has been, a major electronics player. That's their main business. That is where they'll focus. Their directors have stated as much.<br>
<br>
Verant is little more than a glorified sideshow to them.<br>
<br>
If it was a gaming company like Infogrames or EA that owned Verant, you may have slightly better support options, but you have a gaming company owned by an electronics mega-corporation.<br>
<br>
Sorry, really nothing new or unexpected there. It 's a sorry thing, to be sure, but it's to be expected.<br>
